snippet.title: Raising Kids the Right Way | Teach Kids Science | Nature Journals for Kids
snippet.description:
In this episode of Raising Kids the Right Way, Samara learns & teaches the parts of a plant in both English and Bahasa Indonesia!

YES! You can create multi-disciplinary lessons for kids using a cheap, simple, fun, and effective tool like a Nature Journal! We also learn how to use Nature Journals for Kids to Teach Kids Science!

After a field trip to observe the plant Samara learns about flowers, stems, leaves and roots and then teaches her mom in their native language Indonesian.

If you want to connect kids with Nature AND have a lot of fun learning a language, art, and science then outdoor learning with a Nature Journal will help you to Raise Kids Right and Connect them to Nature for a more sustainable and eco-friendly lifestyle.

snippet.title: NF Forum 2020: The Impact of NF1 on Relationships, Learning, and School
snippet.description:
This NF Forum virtual session was presented on Sept 17, 2020, and discussed the impact of neurofibromatosis on school and learning, with an in depth look at IEPs, learning disabilities, social-emotional issues, and more. 

In collaboration with NYU Langone Health, the Children’s Tumor Foundation hosted its first ever NF1- specific patient and family NF Forum. This four-part event was hosted virtually over Zoom video meetings on June 25th, July 16th, August 13th, and September 17th. 


For more information, go to ctf.org/nfforum

snippet.title: “Concerned About Your Child’s Development?” in ASL
snippet.description:
This video provides information in American Sign Language (ASL) on what to do if you have concerns about your child’s development. Talk with your child’s doctor, share your concerns and ask about developmental screening and services that may help. Don’t wait. Acting early can make a real difference! 

Download CDC’s free Milestone Tracker app from the App Store or Google Play to track your child’s milestones and share a summary and any concerns with the doctor. 

www.cdc.gov/MilestoneTracker

snippet.title: ADLEY finds a PET DiNOSAUR!!  Playing with Mom, hidden dino eggs, Cave Club routine & pretend play
snippet.description:
Hold on Dino Babies!! We're coming to rescue you!!

You can catch more of Cave Club's adventures here!! - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtjlDJv1bBg3NHZnj3B7f6A

LET'S BE FRIENDS -- https://goo.gl/a7ctjJ

HEY EVERYBODY!! Welcome back to the Cave Club!! We have some new members for you to meet! their names are Rockelle and Tryasaurs! Rockelle is the girl doll and Tyra is her dinosaur best friend!! Rockelle and her friend Emberly noticed that there has been sightings of Dino Baby Crystals all over Pirate Island so they wanted to go on an adventure to rescue all of them! I played as Rockelle and my mom played as Emberly. We searched all over the place like up in trees, in the river, and in caves! When we got close to the cave we met up with Tyra who was being played as my dad!! It was so fun grouping up and searching all over the land for new dino babies! We found 3 friends scattered around the island and then we took them home to our treehouse to take care of them! It was so fun playing with these new toys!!
This is an ad for Mattel


Bye vlog *pshhhhh*
